definition.value: An organic disulfide obtained via oxidative dimerisation of coenzyme A.
A dihydroxybenzoate that is the  conjugate base of o-orsellinic acid.
An L-cysteine thioether that is L-cysteine in which the hydrogen of the thiol group has been replaced by a carboxymethyl group.
A  benzenetriol carrying hydroxy groups at positions 1, 2 and 3.
